<subSubSection id="C36E5BFCE407FFD5FF3DFD90841BF853" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" type="key">
<keyStep id="308010D2E407FFD5FF3DFD908418FDE0" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF3DFD908418FD84" blockId="5.[208,1380,519,600]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF3DFD908418FD84" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
1. Stipule glabrous to subglabrous abaxially, sparse hairs present at margin and dense at base adaxially or only at apex abaxially, sometimes hairy only along midline; netted veins conspicuous 
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FBF7FDB38518FD83" box="[1050,1121,548,571]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">in sicco</emphasis>
................................. 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF3DFDD68418FDE0" blockId="5.[208,1380,519,600]" box="[208,1377,576,600]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF3DFDD68418FDE0" box="[208,1377,576,600]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
— Stipule hairy abaxially throughout; netted veins inconspicuous 
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FC68FDD682B2FDE0" box="[901,971,577,600]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">in sicco</emphasis>
.......................................................... 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308010D2E407FFD5FF3DFDE3841AFD7D" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF3DFDE38418FD34" blockId="5.[208,1379,628,709]" box="[208,1377,628,652]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF3DFDE38418FD34" box="[208,1377,628,652]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">2. Petiole glabrous to the naked eye; inflorescence pedunculate umbellate; Viêtnam ........................................ 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF3DFD06841AFD7D" blockId="5.[208,1379,628,709]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF3DFD06841AFD7D" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
— Petiole hairy to the naked eye on canalicular ridges; inflorescence sessile umbellate; Cambodia ...................... ............................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7473F4E407FFD5FD79FD3A8473FD7D" authority="Yooprasert, Culham &amp; Utteridge" authorityName="Yooprasert, Culham &amp; Utteridge" authorityYear="2022" box="[660,1290,685,709]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulchristipulum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FD79FD3A82D4FD7D" box="[660,941,685,709]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Urophyllum pulchristipulum</emphasis>
Yooprasert, Culham &amp; Utteridge
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A233691EE407FFD5FAF9FD39841AFD7D" box="[1300,1379,686,709]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308010D2E407FFD5FF3DFD76841AFCF6" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF3DFD76841AFCAD" blockId="5.[208,1379,736,847]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF3DFD76841AFCAD" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
3. Stipule glabrous to subglabrous with hairs only at the apex ............................................................................ ................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C7473F4E407FFD5FD28FD6A8473FCAD" authority="Yooprasert, Culham &amp; Utteridge" authorityName="Yooprasert, Culham &amp; Utteridge" authorityYear="2022" box="[709,1290,765,789]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bidoupense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FD28FD6A82D4FCAD" box="[709,941,765,789]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Urophyllum bidoupense</emphasis>
Yooprasert, Culham &amp; Utteridge
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A233691EE407FFD5FAF9FD69841AFCAD" box="[1300,1379,766,789]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF3DFC8D841AFCF6" blockId="5.[208,1379,736,847]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF3DFC8D841AFCF6" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
— Stipule hairy along the midline from base to apex .......................................................................................... ........................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7473F4E407FFD5FE48FCA0859FFCF7" authority="Yooprasert, Culham, Yahara &amp; Utteridge" authorityName="Yooprasert, Culham, Yahara &amp; Utteridge" authorityYear="2022" box="[421,1254,823,847]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="chinense" status="subsp. nov." subSpecies="latistipulum">
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FE48FCA0830DFCF7" box="[421,628,823,847]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Urophyllum chinense</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FD2CFCA08240FCF7" box="[705,825,823,847]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">latistipulum</emphasis>
Yooprasert, Culham, Yahara &amp; Utteridge
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A233691EE407FFD5FB1DFCA0841AFCF6" box="[1264,1379,823,847]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" rank="subSpecies">subsp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308010D2E407FFD5FF3DFCFD8418FC26" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF3DFCFD8418FC3A" blockId="5.[208,1377,874,927]" box="[208,1377,874,898]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF3DFCFD8418FC3A" box="[208,1377,874,898]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">4. Petiole hairs conspicuously denser on canalicular ridges, sometimes hairy only on the ridges ....................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF3DFC108418FC26" blockId="5.[208,1377,874,927]" box="[208,1377,903,927]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF3DFC108418FC26" box="[208,1377,903,927]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">— Petiole hairs similar density all over ............................................................................................................... 7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308010D2E407FFD5FF3DFC2D8418FB90" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF3DFC2D8418FC57" blockId="5.[208,1380,954,1065]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF3DFC2D8418FC57" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
5. Stipule margin with hairs denser than other areas; petiole hairy throughout, but with hairs along canalicular ridges distinctly paler and contrasting ........................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7473F4E407FFD5FC76FC408418FC57" authority="F. C. How ex H. S. Lo" authorityName="H. S. Lo" box="[923,1377,983,1007]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parviflorum">
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FC76FC4085F7FC57" box="[923,1166,983,1007]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Urophyllum parviflorum</emphasis>
F.C.How ex H.S.Lo
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF10FC638418FB90" blockId="5.[208,1380,954,1065]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF10FC638418FB90" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Stipule hair density similar throughout; petioles variously hairy, but hairs the same colour throughout and without any contrasting colours .................................................................................................................. 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308010D2E407FFD5FF3DFBD38418FB0A" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF3DFBD3841AFBC0" blockId="5.[208,1379,1092,1202]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF3DFBD3841AFBC0" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
6. Staminate inflorescence sessile umbellate; staminodes absent in pistillate flowers; Viêtnam ............................. ................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C7473F4E407FFD5FE02FBF78473FBC0" authority="Yooprasert, Culham, Yahara, Tagane &amp; Utteridge" authorityName="Yooprasert, Culham, Yahara, Tagane &amp; Utteridge" authorityYear="2022" box="[495,1290,1120,1145]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudoschmidtii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FE02FBF7827EFBC0" box="[495,775,1120,1144]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Urophyllum pseudoschmidtii</emphasis>
Yooprasert, Culham, Yahara, Tagane &amp; Utteridge
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A233691EE407FFD5FAF9FBF6841AFBC0" box="[1300,1379,1121,1144]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF10FBEA8418FB0A" blockId="5.[208,1379,1092,1202]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF10FBEA8418FB0A" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
Staminate inflorescence pedunculate umbellate; staminodes present in pistillate flowers; Thailand and Cambodia................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7473F4E407FFD5FBE2FB0D8418FB0A" authority="C. B. Clarke" authorityName="C. B. Clarke" box="[1039,1377,1178,1202]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schmidtii">
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FBE2FB0D859EFB0A" box="[1039,1255,1178,1202]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Urophyllum schmidtii</emphasis>
C.B.Clarke
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308010D2E407FFD5FF3DFB59841BFABA" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF3DFB598418FB5D" blockId="5.[208,1378,1229,1282]" box="[208,1377,1229,1253]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF3DFB598418FB5D" box="[208,1377,1229,1253]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">7. Secondary veins weakly brochidodromous (loops inconspicuous) or eucamptodromous .............................. 8</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF10FB7D841BFABA" blockId="5.[208,1378,1229,1282]" box="[253,1378,1258,1282]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF10FB7D841BFABA" box="[253,1378,1258,1282]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Secondary veins conspicuously brochidodromous or festooned brochidodromous ..................................... 10</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308010D2E407FFD5FF3DFA898418FAD7" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF3DFA89841BFAEA" blockId="5.[208,1378,1309,1391]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF3DFA89841BFAEA" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
8. All parts covered with long sericeous hairs; corolla with sparse sericeous hairs abaxially .................................. ............................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C7473F4E407FFD5FBBEFAAD841BFAEA" authority="Pit." authorityName="Pit." box="[1107,1378,1338,1362]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="argenteum">
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FBBEFAAD844EFAEA" box="[1107,1335,1338,1362]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Urophyllum argenteum</emphasis>
Pit.
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF10FAC08418FAD7" blockId="5.[208,1378,1309,1391]" box="[253,1377,1367,1391]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF10FAC08418FAD7" box="[253,1377,1367,1391]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">All parts subglabrous or covered with hairs but not sericeous; corolla glabrous abaxially .............................. 9</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308010D2E407FFD5FF3DFA1D841AF989" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF3DFA1D841BFA64" blockId="5.[208,1380,1418,1586]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF3DFA1D841BFA64" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
9. Leaves coriaceous, abaxial lamina densely appressed hairy; stipules appressed to the stem, sometimes recurved at margins but not folded; inflorescence single flower or pedunculate umbellate, small number of flowers usually &lt;5; corolla white ............................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7473F4E407FFD5FCBBFA53841BFA64" authority="subsp. chinense Merr. &amp; Chun" authorityName="Merr. &amp; Chun" box="[854,1378,1476,1500]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="chinense" subSpecies="chinense">
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FCBBFA53855DFA64" box="[854,1060,1476,1500]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Urophyllum chinense</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FB9FFA5385BAFA64" box="[1138,1219,1476,1500]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">chinense</emphasis>
Merr. &amp; Chun
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF10FA76841AF989" blockId="5.[208,1380,1418,1586]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF10FA76841AF989" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
Leaves chartaceous, abaxial lamina glabrous; stipule folded toward adaxial side; inflorescence compound cymose, many flowers&gt; 7; corolla green ...................................................................................................................... .......................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C7473F4E407FFD5FDF6F98D8585F98A" authority="(Pierre ex Pit.) Yooprasert, Culham &amp; Utteridge" authorityName="Yooprasert, Culham &amp; Utteridge" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Pierre ex Pit." box="[539,1276,1562,1586]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="annamense" status="stat. nov.">
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FDF6F98D827CF98A" box="[539,773,1562,1586]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Urophyllum annamense</emphasis>
(Pierre ex Pit.) Yooprasert, Culham &amp; Utteridge
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A233691EE407FFD5FAEBF98D841AF989" box="[1286,1379,1562,1585]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308010D2E407FFD5FF3DF9DA841BF94D" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF3DF9DA8418F927" blockId="5.[208,1380,1613,1781]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF3DF9DA8418F927" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
10. Adaxial leaf veins glabrous; leaf reddish brown 
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FD19F9D98242F9DD" box="[756,827,1614,1637]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">in sicco</emphasis>
; tertiary veins not prominent, inconspicuous abaxially; inflorescence peduncle long 
<quantity id="4C8CA592E407FFD5FDBCF9FD83CCF93A" box="[593,693,1642,1666]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.0">5-10 mm</quantity>
, sparsely hairy; abaxial corolla surface glabrous.............................. ....................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C7473F4E407FFD5FC58F9108418F927" authority="F. C. How ex H. S. Lo" authorityName="H. S. Lo" box="[949,1377,1671,1695]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tsaianum">
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FC58F91085F6F926" box="[949,1167,1671,1695]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Urophyllum tsaianum</emphasis>
F.C.How ex H.S.Lo
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF10F934841BF94D" blockId="5.[208,1380,1613,1781]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF10F934841BF94D" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
Adaxial leaf veins hairy, sometimes only on midrib; leaf yellowish or greenish brown to dark grey 
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FB2AF9338472F903" box="[1223,1291,1700,1723]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">in sicco</emphasis>
; tertiary veins prominent, conspicuous abaxially; inflorescence peduncle short or sessile 
<quantity id="4C8CA592E407FFD5FBF5F95785F8F960" box="[1048,1153,1728,1752]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" unit="mm" value="1.45" valueMax="2.9" valueMin="0.0">0-2.9 mm</quantity>
, densely hairy; abaxial corolla surface hairy .................................................................................................................................. 11
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308010D2E407FFD5FF3DF887841BF823" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF3DF887841AF8D9" blockId="5.[208,1379,1808,1947]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF3DF887841AF8D9" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
11. Mature leaves with secondary veins hairy adaxially, brochidodromous without a series of small loops outside the main loop or inconspicuous; flower and fruit calyx lobes recurved ............................................................ .......................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C7473F4E407FFD5FD6AF8DD8473F8DA" authority="Yooprasert, Culham &amp; Utteridge" authorityName="Yooprasert, Culham &amp; Utteridge" authorityYear="2022" box="[647,1290,1866,1890]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brochidodromum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FD6AF8DD82D4F8DA" box="[647,941,1866,1890]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Urophyllum brochidodromum</emphasis>
Yooprasert, Culham &amp; Utteridge
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A233691EE407FFD5FAF9F8DD841AF8D9" box="[1300,1379,1866,1889]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF10F8F0841BF823" blockId="5.[208,1379,1808,1947]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF10F8F0841BF823" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Mature leaves with secondary veins glabrous, brochidodromous with a series of small loops (festooned); flower and fruit calyx lobes erect or folded toward adaxial side ............................................................................. 12</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308010D2E407FFD5FF3DF820841BF853" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF3DF820841BF877" blockId="5.[208,1378,1975,2027]" box="[208,1378,1975,1999]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF3DF820841BF877" box="[208,1378,1975,1999]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
12. Pistillate plant with pedunculate umbellate inflorescence .......................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C7473F4E407FFD5FB87F820841BF877" authority="Pit." authorityName="Pit." box="[1130,1378,1975,1999]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lecomtei">
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FB87F820844EF877" box="[1130,1335,1975,1999]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Urophyllum lecomtei</emphasis>
Pit.
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E407FFD5FF10F844841BF853" blockId="5.[208,1378,1975,2027]" box="[253,1378,2003,2027]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<keyLead id="3085AB42E407FFD5FF10F844841BF853" box="[253,1378,2003,2027]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
Pistillate plant with sessile umbellate inflorescence ................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7473F4E407FFD5FBBFF844841BF853" authority="Pit." authorityName="Pit." box="[1106,1378,2003,2027]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tonkinense">
<emphasis id="B900D465E407FFD5FBBFF844844EF853" box="[1106,1335,2003,2027]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Urophyllum tonkinense</emphasis>
Pit.
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
